  "title": "Project Engineer #67897",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Manufacturing/ Chemical</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Project Engineer</strong></li><li>Working Location: Tuas (walk distance from MRT)</li><li>Working Hours: 5 Days (Mon – Fri, 8.30AM – 5.30PM)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Allowances + AWS + VB</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in preparing Requests for Quotations (RFQs) and coordinate project planning activities.</li><li>Liaise with contractors, suppliers, and vendors to address and resolve project-related issues, ensuring smooth communication and operations.</li><li>Verify that all project work adheres to quality and safety standards, conducting inspections and audits as necessary.</li><li>Monitor and manage the project section's budget, tracking expenditures and identifying cost-saving opportunities.</li><li>Prepare and maintain project documentation, including technical drawings, progress reports, and compliance records.</li><li>Assist in supervising and carry out company’s EHS related activities.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Electrical, Mechanical, or Chemical Engineering.</li><li>At least 2 years of experience in a relevant field.</li><li>General understanding of electrical system (Possess a LEW license is an added advantage).</li><li>With knowledge on Risk Assessment and Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (FMEA).</li><li>Preferably with AutoCAD software knowledge.</li><li>Good knowledge of Environment, Health and Safety, and ISO14001, 45001 standards.</li><li>Competent with Microsoft Words, Excel and PowerPoint.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#67897 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
